about.description:
mpmath is a free Python library for real and complex floating-point
arithmetic with arbitrary precision.
about.summary: Python library for arbitrary-precision floating-point arithmetic

name: mpmath
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.1.0" %}

package:
  name: mpmath
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/m/mpmath/mpmath-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: fc17abe05fbab3382b61a123c398508183406fa132e0223874578e20946499f6

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - mpmath
    - mpmath.calculus
    - mpmath.functions
    - mpmath.libmp
    - mpmath.matrices
    - mpmath.tests

about:
  home: http://mpmath.org
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Python library for arbitrary-precision floating-point arithmetic
  description: |
    mpmath is a free Python library for real and complex floating-point
    arithmetic with arbitrary precision.
  doc_url: http://mpmath.org/doc/current/
  dev_url: https://github.com/fredrik-johansson/mpmath

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - asmeurer
    - msarahan
    - ocefpaf
    - scopatz
